2. nam Tiberius: there has' been no indication thus far of any unfriendly feeling towards the sons of Germanicus, and on the present occasion the remarks of Tiberius to the senate were wise and sagacious. We see here, however, the begin- nings of that jealous suspicion of Agrippina which may have been well founded, and which, at any rate, poisoned the aged emperor's mind during the last years of her life.
